[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Jameson is a 39 year-old male that presented with rectal bleeding on-and-off x 2 months. Patient had a colonoscopy 1/14/2010 and it revealed an ulcerated fungating malignancy in the rectum along the posterior wall extending off the right-side of the rectum. The mass took up one-third of the rectal lumen and began at less than 5-cm from the anal verge.  Patient under went neoadjuvant chemotherapy and radiation. Initially seen with Dr. Knox in March who discussed the need for Total Proctocolectomy with Permanent Ileostomy.   Now returns for surgery. Seen again with Dr. Knox who reviewed surgery.

[end section id="20103"]

