[start section id="20109"]

Family pedigree will be scanned under the patient's medical record.
Pertinent findings:  Maternal grandfather died at age 88 of natural causes.  No known history of cancer.  Maternal grandmother died at age 86 of Alzheimer's without known history of cancer.  Mother, age 64, was diagnosed with endometrial cancer at age 60 and underwent hysterectomy with oophorectomy, radiation therapy.  She was found to have one benign colon polyp per colonoscopy; however, the histology of that is not known.  Maternal aunt, age 70, had hysterectomy in her 40s because of bleeding.  No history of cancer.
No other individuals on the maternal side of the family with colon cancer, biliary tract or genitourinary tract cancers, or ovarian cancers.
Paternal grandparents died in their mid-60s of myocardial infarction.  No history of cancer.  Paternal uncle died at age 59 of prostate cancer diagnosed at age 57.  No other cancer history on the paternal side of the family.
Sister, age 40, has not undergone colonoscopy.  No other individuals in the family with known abnormal results of colonoscopy.

